The Diploma in the “Administration, Finance and Marketing” has general competence in the field of macro-phenomena of economic, national and international, of the civil law, and fiscal, systems, and processes of the enterprise (organization, planning, programming, administration, finance and control), marketing tools, products, insurance, financial and social economy. Integrates the skills of the professional domain specific languages and computer science to operate in the information system of the company and contribute both to the innovation is to improve the organization and technology of the company entered in an international context.
 Through the general path, you can:
 - Track operations management by using methods, tools, techniques, accounting and off-balance-sheet in line with the principles of national and international;
 - write and interpret documents the administrative and financial business;
 - manage compliance of a fiscal nature;
 - assist with contract negotiations related to the different functional areas of the company;
 - carry out marketing activities;
 - assist in the organization, management and control of business processes;
 - use technologies and software applications for the integrated management of administration, finance and marketing.

The Diploma of vocational education in the address “Maintenance and technical assistance” has the skills to manage, organize and carry out installation and routine maintenance, diagnostic, repair, and testing of relatively small systems, equipment and technical devices, and also maritime. Its technical and professional skills are related to the sectors of the productive sectors in general (electronics, electrical engineering, mechanical engineering, heat engineering and others) and specifically developed in relation to the needs expressed by the community.
 Is able to:
 - check and repair during the life cycle of the equipment and facility, the compliance of their operation to the technical specifications and regulations on the safety of users and the protection of the environment;
 - observe the principles of ergonomics, safety and hygiene regulations governing the implementation of the interventions;
 - organize and participate in activities for the disposal of waste and residual substances, related to the operation of the machines, and for the disposal of the devices;
 - use the multi-disciplinary skills in the context of technological, economic and organisational present in the working processes, and services that involve;
 - functionally manage the inventory and the procedures for the procurement;
 - assist users and provide useful information on the proper use and operation of the devices;
 - acting in its scope of intervention in accordance with the specific regulations and take autonomous responsibility.

